### GET /admin/campaigns

This endpoint retrieves a list of campaigns based on the provided filters and pagination parameters.

**Request Parameters:**
- `paginationCounter` (string, optional): The pagination counter.
- `page` (string, optional): The page number.
- `sortColumn` (string, optional): The column to sort by.
- `sortDirection` (string, optional): The direction for sorting.
- `dateFrom` (string, optional): The start date for filtering.
- `dateTo` (string, optional): The end date for filtering.
- `campaign_id` (string, optional): The ID of the campaign.
- `campaign_title` (string, optional): The title of the campaign.
- `campaign_status` (string, optional): The status of the campaign.
- `campaign_description` (string, optional): The description of the campaign.
- `start_at` (string, optional): The start date of the campaign.
- `close_at` (string, optional): The end date of the campaign.
- `conditions` (string, optional): The conditions for the campaign.
- `product_image` (string, optional): The image of the product.
- `ugc_no` (string, optional): The UGC number.
- `ugc_videos_no` (string, optional): The number of UGC videos.
- `video_seconds_min` (string, optional): The minimum duration of the video.
- `video_seconds_max` (string, optional): The maximum duration of the video.
- `video_price` (string, optional): The price of the video.
- `total_price` (string, optional): The total price.
- `is_usg_show` (string, optional): Indicates if UGC is shown.
- `is_brand_show` (string, optional): Indicates if the brand is shown.
- `is_tiktok` (string, optional): Indicates if TikTok is used.
- `is_instagram` (string, optional): Indicates if Instagram is used.
- `is_youtube` (string, optional): Indicates if YouTube is used.
- `is_sent_to_content_creator` (string, optional): Indicates if sent to content creator.
- `deleted_at` (string, optional): The deletion date.
- `created_at` (string, optional): The creation date.

